The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 22 October is 86,712 (9,994.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 17 October, there were 3,571 new confirmed cases (411.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 10 October, there were 2,638 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 35% (933 extra cases).
